        '{"type": "TextualBody", "value": "1C transl. Instead of saying “μνημονεύω τοῦ δεῖνος [I remember so-and-so]”, they say “διὰ μνήμης ἔχω τὸν δεῖνα [I have so-and-so in memory]”. In the same way, they say: “διὰ φροντίδος ἔχω τὸν δεῖνα [I have so-and-so in thought]” and “δι᾿ ἀγάπης [with/ in love]” and “δι᾿ ἀμελείας [with/ in neglect]” and “δι᾿ ἐπαίνου [with/ in praise]” and “διὰ ψόγου [with/ in blame]”, instead of “φρονέω [I think]”, “ἀγαπῶ [I love]”, “ἀμελῶ [I neglect]”, “ἐπαινῶ [I approve]”, “ψέγω [I blame]”.", "format": "text", "source": "mela:text-content:7045f9d1-6135-4eb9-bd13-19ce1d7a86bc", "language": "en"}',
        '77c07513-c1ab-4ebe-be00-aabf4609f751', null, null),
